The federal government on Wednesday flagged off the Extended Special Public Work programme of the National Directorate of Employment (NDE) tagged “Temporary employment of 774,000 youths and the disbursement of N20,000 to each of the beneficiaries for three months in Bauchi State. It would be recalled that the scheme, which entails temporary employment of 774,000 youths across the 774 Local Government Areas in the country, and the disbursement of N20,000 to each of the beneficiaries for three months, was conceived by the Minister of State, Labour and Employment, Festus Keyamo. Declaring the programme open in Bauchi state, the Acting Director General of the National Directorate of Employment,Mallam Abubakar Nuhu Fikpo said that the Programme was implemented in eight states of the Federation to address unemployment and insecurity issues in some parts of the country. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He said that president Muhammadu Buhari had approved for the implementation of the Programme to all 36 stated of the federation after the successful conduct of the pilot phase of the Programme within the first quarter of 2020 in 8 states including Adamawa, Borno, Ebonyi, Edo, Ekiti, Jigawa, Katsina and Kwara states, adding that the Special public works was an outcome of extended activities to rural area approved by President Buhari and implemented by National Directorate of Employment, NDE in early 2020. “This strategy was adopted to fast track the achievement of the Economic Recovery and Growth Plan (2017-2020).However, to cushion the effect of COVID-19,the federal government also directed the Ministry of Labour and Employment to adopt a proactive measure by engaging in some important economic sector” NSCDC Records 1,922 Criminal Cases In Jigawa Nigeria To Participate In African Weightlifting Championships In Mauritius “The programme is also aimed at shielding the vulnerable from the ravaging effects of COVID-19 pandemic which includes hunger, poverty, environmental degradation and joblessness.The federal government target is to engage 20,000 selected unemployed indegenes of Bauchi State to execute selected projects across 20 local government areas.1,000 youths were selected from each local government to make up the 20,000 beneficiaries” he said Abubakar explained that the federal government would closely monitor the implementation of the programme to ascertain the efficient utilisation of resources committed to the programme even as he solicited for more support in ensuring effective implementation of the programme across 20 local government areas of the Bauchi State. He charged all the participants to reciprocate the gesture of the President Muhammadu Buhari, (GCFR) led Government by diligently executing their assigned tasks throughout the duration of the programme. In his address at the occasion, the Bauchi State Governor, Bala Abdulkadri Mohammed who was represented by the State Commissioner for Small, medium enterprises and poverty Alleviation, Modibbo Ahmed applauded federal government for initiating the programme that would assist in lifting Nigerians out of poverty. He reiterated the State government’s commitments towards collaboration with NDE to ensure smooth implementation of the programme across the twenty local government areas in the State. The governor urged the beneficiaries to take advantage of the programme to improve their socio-economic status.